Monthly FX Requirements
7.1 Standard Partner Behavior
• Compute monthly average from daily FX values for the given month
OR
• Compute rolling N month average (e.g., average of Jan + Feb if running in March).
7.2 AMEX Canada Behavior
• Use N months
• For each of the previous N calendar months: 
o Take only the last business day FX rate
• Average these N final-day values
• Example:
If N=2 and today = March → use: 
o Feb last-day FX
o Jan last-day FX
→ average of those 2 values

Calculation: 
Day exchangeRate (big number) decimalPoint realRate
Day 1 1425923… 33 1425.923
Day 2 1420000… 33 1420
Day 3 1431000… 33 1431
• 
• 1425.9232 +1420.0000 +1431.0000 = 4276.9232
• 4276.9232 / 3 = 1425.641066...
• realRate = outputCurrencyExchangeRate ÷ (10 ^ outputCurrencyDecimalPoint) monthlyAverage = (rate1 + rate2 + rate3 + ... ) ÷ numberOfDays


7.3 Date Range Constraintsg
• TIP only supports last 2 years.
• Contract ranges (e.g., 2023–2029) may demand FX for months TIP cannot serve → fallback or manual solution required.

Required Inputs for Monthly Run
1. Partner list where fx_rate_service_type = Automated
2. Base/quote currency pairs per partner
3. Partner’s FX configuration: 
o fx_avg_months_num
o Average method (standard vs AMEX)
4. For each month/day in scope: 
o TIP daily rate (calculated using formula)

Required Outputs
For each base/quote pair:
• Computed monthly average FX
• Stored row in lfs_ref_forex_monthly_avg_rate with: 
o Rate
o Year
o Month
o Audit JSON including calculation method, dates included/excluded, TZ, version, etc.

Known Constraints
• TIP API fails for dates >2 years in past. – better we should process less than that range only.
• TIP returns same value for weekends. – so we don’t needed to care of it and use the values and average for month.
• FX daily boundary must be treated in ET. – so we will be using the EST time zone as the service also be running on us so no needed to care of it.
• Cannot run daily ingestion (for now); monthly only. – now we have to give approaches with day & month and then lets see what product decides to go with.
• Monthly jobs must wait until final day’s FX is considered stable. – yes since it’s a monthly average it has to be run monthly and if day wise we have to handle in such a way. So lets give approaches and lets modify the design after the confirmation of approach.
 
